The paper deals with deep convolutional neural networks for image recognition, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of these networks for generalization to other datasets, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of weight layers, which could fall under neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the models on different datasets, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM).
